      "content": "that makes sense. but i'm curious, when people talk about those areas being \"dangerous\" or \"high crime,\" is that because of the actual crime stats, or is it more about the vibe/demographics of the people living there? like, do the residents themselves feel less safe, or is it just a perception based on the racial makeup of those neighborhoods?",
